# ScrapCo V2 — System Architecture

## 1. Architecture Overview

ScrapCo V2 is a scalable, event-driven, queue-based marketplace platform built to support multi-city expansion without architectural redesign.

The system is composed of:

- Web Application (Next.js)
- Mobile Application (Expo React Native)
- Backend API (Node.js / NestJS preferred)
- Background Worker Service (Queue Processor)
- PostgreSQL Database (Supabase)
- Redis (Queue + Caching + Coordination)
- Real-Time Gateway (WebSocket or Supabase Realtime)
- External Services (Push Notifications, Monitoring)

The architecture must support:

- Horizontal scaling
- Multi-instance backend
- Stateless API layer
- Stateful dispatch managed via Redis + DB
- Zero in-memory critical logic

